# SECTION 01 — MODELING PHILOSOPHY

## Core Principle

The semantic model exists to support business decisions.

The model must not be driven by source systems.

The model must be driven by decision requirements.

---

## Incorrect Design Approach

```text
Source Tables
↓
Columns
↓
Relationships
↓
Dashboard
```

---

## Correct Design Approach

```text
Decision
↓
Business Question
↓
Signal
↓
Measure
↓
Grain
↓
Fact
↓
Dimension
↓
Semantic Model
```

---

## Model Success Criteria

A semantic model is successful when:

```text
Every Measure supports a Signal.

Every Signal supports a Business Question.

Every Business Question supports a Decision.

Every Decision supports Action.
```

---

# SECTION 02 — DECISION TRACEABILITY

## Purpose

Maintain complete traceability from business intent to semantic design.

---

## Required Traceability Chain

```text
Decision
↓
Business Question
↓
Signal
↓
Measure
↓
Fact
↓
Dimension
↓
Visual
```

---

## Required Traceability Rule

Every measure must support:

```text
At Least One Signal
```

Every signal must support:

```text
At Least One Business Question
```

Every business question must support:

```text
At Least One Decision
```

---

## Decision Traceability Example

```text
Decision

Can this centre receive another animal?

↓

Signal

Remaining Capacity

↓

Measure

Available Spaces

↓

Fact

Fact_Capacity

↓

Visual

Intake Readiness
```

---

# SECTION 03 — GRAIN-FIRST DESIGN

## Governing Rule

Always define grain before creating a fact table.

Fact tables must never determine their own grain.

---

## Grain Definition

Grain answers:

```text
What does one row represent?
```

---

## Examples

### Good

```text
Centre
+
Date
+
Animal Type
```

### Good

```text
Animal
+
Centre
+
Date
```

### Bad

```text
Capacity
+
Occupancy
```

within the same row without explicit definition.

---

## Grain Declaration Rule

Every fact table must document:

```text
Business Grain

Business Purpose

Example Row
```

---

## Grain Validation Test

Ask:

```text
Can every row be described in one sentence?
```

Example:

```text
One row represents centre capacity
for a specific date and animal type.
```

